---
// About the Trials — Michael's own words, links made clickable.
import TrialsLayout from "../../layouts/TrialsLayout.astro";
const crumbs = [
  { href: "/trials/", label: "← Trials" },
  { href: "/schedule/", label: "Event schedule →" },
];
---

<TrialsLayout
  title="About · Vibecamp Trials"
  description="How the Vibecamp Trials are going down — shifts, signups, badges, and what to expect."
  crumbs={crumbs}
>
  <header class="trials-hero">
    <p class="kicker">✦ Vibecamp Trials</p>
    <h1>About</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="board">
  <section class="t-prose pinned" style="--ac: var(--peach); --tilt: -0.6deg">
    <h2>How is this going down?</h2>
    <p>
      I'll start Friday morning. There will be shifts
      throughout the weekend. Two shifts Friday/Saturday, and one final shift on
      Sunday morning for late turn-ins. New players may sign up at any of the
      Friday/Saturday shifts, but not on Sunday. Please read the schedule entries
      to confirm these details. Please also note, each of the shifts is at a
      different location, make sure you're headed to the right place.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are also encouraged to use
      <a href="/schedule/">vibecamp.mahan.io/schedule</a> to figure out your
      general Vibecamp schedule!
    </p>
    <p>
      The estimate for time is about 1–2 hours per person. Some of the trials are
      collaborative, and I'll have lengths of ribbon you can tie to your lanyard
      to showcase that you're participating, and so you can find other
      participants.
    </p>
    <p>
      There will be items hidden around the grounds, inside of existing
      structures. The trials are of varying difficulties, and they may be done in
      any order.
    </p>
    <p>
      Everyone who signs up will receive a badge case, that's yours for free!
      The badges will require proof of accomplishment, and what that is will be
      outlined in a handout acquired at time of signup. A copy of all documents
      will be available on the <a href="/trials/documents/">documents page</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      This event took most of the last year to throw together, and was frankly
      quite expensive — if you'd like to chip in, see the
      <a href="/trials/donate/">donate page</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you're interested in contacting me regarding running similar events, hit
      me up at <a href="mailto:studio@mahan.io">studio@mahan.io</a>. You may
      also locate me on twitter
      <a href="https://twitter.com/timebard" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@timebard</a>,
      though I check email more than DMs.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      Websites were done at my direction by Claude. Badge designs are by &lt;&gt;.
      Puzzle assistance done by
      <a href="https://twitter.com/thrialectics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@thrialectics</a>.
      Planning and development, resourcing, and final touches by myself.
    </p>
  </section>
  </div>
</TrialsLayout>
